  "title": "Senior Product Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the delivery and maintenance of operational systems</li><li>Plan the roadmap for operational systems and priorities the rollout of features according to business needs</li><li>Manage a team of outsourced IT professionals, providing leadership, coaching, and mentorship to ensure that the team is motivated, skilled, and aligned with operational goals</li><li>Manage all Production issues and then review those with relevant PM, and then prioritise accordingly with relevant Stakeholders.</li><li>Coordinate with the Engineering department to deliver functional solutions</li><li>Collaborate with business leaders to comprehend their needs and create technology solutions that can further their objectives</li><li>Ensure that operational systems are secure, compliant with regulatory requirements, and aligned with industry best practices</li><li>Keep up with emerging technologies and trends in the local land transportation industry and provide thought leadership to the organization</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Business, Economics, Information Technology, and related fields</li><li>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience</li><li>Good grasp and exposure to a range of software development life cycle methodology (e.g. Agile, Waterfall)</li><li>Able to distill large complex user problems into smaller user stories</li><li>Good understanding of UX concepts for wireframe preparation (e.g. Figma, Miro, Balsamiq)</li><li>Ability to effectively translate business requirements into technical requirements, and vice versa</li><li>Basic data querying, manipulation (e.g. MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc) & visualization skills (e.g. PowerBI, SAS, etc)</li><li>Experience managing an entire product lifecycle</li><li>Has hands-on experience with web technologies</li><li>Knowledge of project management tools such as Jira or Trello</li><li>Has the ability to drive results and outcomes through effective leadership</li></ul>",
